children.value: I need people I can rely on.

children.name: Text
children.value: Hard to fit you into my vision.

children.name: Text
children.value: Friends of mine should strive to be exceptional.

children.name: Text
children.value: Our friends are our stepping stones.

children.name: Text
children.value: We stand astride the shoulders of our friends.

children.name: Text
children.value: You are rubbing up the wrong balustrade.

children.name: Text
children.value: Don't make ripples in the pond!

children.name: Text
children.value: My friends all have a lot of influence on the scene.

children.name: Text
children.value: So you heard they were one of my critics?

children.name: Text
children.value: Be careful where you cast your shadow…

children.name: Text
children.value: Creeping up my esteemed friend's stair.

children.name: Text
children.value: A concealed antechamber in the house of your enemy.

children.name: Text
children.value: Important to seek new perspectives on one's rivals...

children.name: Text
children.value: Spires gleam bright for myself also!

children.name: Text
children.value: I have also been making progress, well done.

children.name: Text
children.value: Some like a brash colonial style.

children.name: Text
children.value: I love snipping the tape on a new wing!

children.name: Text
children.value: Broaden the boulevards, let in the light!

children.name: Text
children.value: And my critics say I don't take enough risks.

children.name: Text
children.value: I can appreciate the art of others.

children.name: Text
children.value: The therapist says money matters dominate middle age.

children.name: Text
children.value: I'll make sure it has a smooth finish.

children.name: Text
children.value: Maybe losing your island will polish you off?

children.name: Text
children.value: Don't lurk as if I am somehow past it!

children.name: Text
children.value: What? I can't afford one of my pieces!

children.name: Text
children.value: I firmly believe art should be shared by all.

children.name: Text
children.value: You will never fully appreciate it!

children.name: Text
children.value: You will turn majesty into a monstrosity.

children.name: Text
children.value: Even a featureless desert can be Eden in the right hands.

children.name: Text
children.value: This island is clay, and I am its sculptor.
